# Yawp Licensing

This repository contains code under **two different licenses**. The split lives at
the app boundary inside the Mix umbrella:

| Path                  | License                                           | File                                |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `apps/yawp/`          | GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0) | [`apps/yawp/LICENSE`](apps/yawp/LICENSE)                 |
| `apps/yawp_premium/`  | Proprietary — All rights reserved                 | [`apps/yawp_premium/LICENSE`](apps/yawp_premium/LICENSE) |

## Core — `apps/yawp/`

The core Yawp project (everything required to run a self-hosted, federated,
end-to-end-encrypted Yawp instance) is licensed under the **GNU Affero General
Public License, version 3.0**. See [`apps/yawp/LICENSE`](apps/yawp/LICENSE) for the
full text. The AGPL-3.0 obliges anyone who modifies and runs the software as a
network service to make their modifications available to users of that service.

## Premium — `apps/yawp_premium/`

The `apps/yawp_premium/` tree is **proprietary**, copyright Simon Ricard, all rights
reserved. It is **NOT** licensed under the AGPL-3.0. It exists in this repository
for development convenience and clarity of separation — it is not free software,
and no rights are granted to use, modify, or redistribute it. See
[`apps/yawp_premium/LICENSE`](apps/yawp_premium/LICENSE) for the full notice.

## Cross-tree boundary

**No code from `apps/yawp/` may be copied into `apps/yawp_premium/`, and no code
from `apps/yawp_premium/` may be copied into `apps/yawp/`, without explicit
relicensing by the copyright holder.** The two trees are deliberately quarantined
so the licenses cannot bleed into each other.

## Contributing

See [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](CONTRIBUTING.md). External contributions are accepted to
`apps/yawp/` (subject to a Contributor License Agreement signed via CLA Assistant
and a DCO `Signed-off-by` line). External contributions to `apps/yawp_premium/`
are not accepted.
